
-Doesnt make sense to ask "Do you want to enter your starting trump cards? (y/n)"
 > y

 No trump cards in hand.

 Options:
  +  Add trump card(s)
  -  Remove a trump card (by number)
  c  Clear all
  Enter  Done

You always begin with trumps in survival and survival+
Just begin assume y will always be pressed in the first round (Literally called STARTING TRUMP CARDS)

-Change yellow text to a more visible color

- add memory for current hands.  Change when trumps played disrupt current hands

-I messed up / misinterpreted the wording for remembering cards 2 examples of it happening below. Fix wording and logic:
I had a 7 face down 4 1. Should not be able to change face down card unless a trump card changes that.

- regular 21 still shows 10 health for enemies not 5.

-Hoffman is missing the letter n at the end in some strings

- when recording game state ask the user prompts in the order they happen (opponent plays trump/s record and then prompt the user for what happened in order depending on which trump is played/take into consideration what has happened for next calculations and updating game state)
 better than remembering every move after the play (follow game logic for question order)
- remove challenge lab until it works with logic not just print a guide
 1. Defeat the Elusive Mr. Big Head ( Already logic for this challenge this is just a priority list on which to unlock first )
    Shouldnt even be a challenge lab option just account for his appearences in survival+
 2. Beat Survival without taking damage
 3. Use 15+ trump cards in a single round (impossible until Harvest + Trump Switch is unlocked)
^ only 3 challenges that needs to be focused on to lessen the luck factor in beating 21+ (every other challenge should be unlocked by the time you are able to beat 21+ unless you get an extremely lucky run)

